signals.name: @izuchatel: .@magicblock is tackling one of the quiet limits of building on Solana. Automati
signals.content:
.@magicblock is tackling one of the quiet limits of building on Solana. Automation does not exist natively. Nothing runs unless someone sends a transaction.

That is fine for swaps and mints, it breaks the moment an app needs time based logic.

Game loops, auctions, subscriptions, auto compounding. All of this usually ends up on offchain scripts that developers have to keep alive.

#MagicBlock native cranks move this back onchain.

Cranks let programs schedule instructions to run every N millise
